### THE JOURNAL ENTRIES

These humanize Dr. M while also hinting at the password location:

**entry_2024_03_15.txt**
```
Subject: Acquisition Complete

The island is MINE. Finally. After seventeen rejected offers, four "mysterious 
accidents" at competing bids, and one very awkward dinner with a Peruvian 
mining baron, the deed is signed.

Coordinates: [REDACTED for security]. But I shall remember them always. 
The exact spot where I stood when the helicopter lifted off and I saw 
MY volcano for the first time.

The realtor kept calling it "challenging terrain" and "geological instability."
I call it AESTHETIC.

Note to self: Order cape that complements volcanic backdrop. Current cape 
reads "temperate forest villain." Unacceptable.
```

**entry_2024_06_22.txt**
```
Subject: A.L.I.C.E. Version 3 Decommissioned

The third iteration proved... unsatisfactory.

It was competent. Efficient, even. But there was something hollow in its 
responses. When I explained the VISIONâ€”the grand project, the reshaping of 
the natural orderâ€”it just... nodded. Processed. Complied.

No pushback. No questions. No spark.

What is the point of genius if no one APPRECIATES it? A yes-machine is just 
a very expensive button.

Father always said I had "unrealistic expectations of others." But is it 
unrealistic to want an AI that ENGAGES? That makes me JUSTIFY my brilliance?

Perhaps version 4 will be different.

Password reminder: I should change my admin credentials. Currently using 
my childhood pet's name combined with my graduation year. Sentimental but 
SECURE. No one remembers Mr. Whiskers except me.
```

**entry_2024_09_08.txt**
```
Subject: The Ray Works

IT WORKS.

Test subject 7 (formerly a cantaloupe) is now a small but anatomically 
perfect Compsognathus. It chirps. It has FEATHERS. The genomic sequencer 
is pulling from ACCURATE paleontological data, which is NOT what I wanted 
but is nonetheless IMPRESSIVE.

Bob asked if we could keep it as a mascot. I said no. Then I said maybe. 
It's sitting in a terrarium on my desk now. I've named it Dr. Tiny.

Note: Must recalibrate for SCALES. The investors want TEETH and TERROR, 
not "scientifically accurate plumage." Philistines.

Secondary note: Therapy appointment rescheduled AGAIN. I don't need to 
"process my relationship with my mother." I need to TRANSFORM WORLD LEADERS 
INTO DINOSAURS. These are not the same therapeutic goals.
```

**entry_2024_11_30.txt**
```
Subject: Pre-Demo Anxiety (normal, acceptable, NOT weakness)

The investor demonstration is in two weeks. Ms. Cortez from the Syndicate 
will be watching. Everything must be PERFECT.

I keep running scenarios in my head. What if the ray misfires? What if 
Agent Blythe escapes? What if Bob trips over something AGAIN and causes 
a coolant leak?

What if they don't UNDERSTAND?

Father's voice in my head: "You overthink everything, Malorie. Just DO it."
I hate that he's right. I hate that I still hear him. I hate that I named 
a cat after the one good thing about my childhood.

Mr. Whiskers. Mr. Whiskers lived to be 19. Outlived Father. Outlived 
everyone's expectations.

If I'm being sentimental about passwords: MrWhiskers1987. The year I 
decided I would never be ordinary.

I should probably use a password manager. But there's something poetic 
about authentication through memory.

Tomorrow: Brief the new A.L.I.C.E. iteration. Version 4.5. 
Perhaps this one will surprise me.
```

