## BOB'S SECRET: THE LOADING INCIDENT

Let me write this as a discoverable piece of lore AND a mechanical lever:

### What Actually Happened (GM Knowledge)

Three weeks ago, during a routine system update, the original A.L.I.C.E. v4.5 crashed hard. Blue screen. Kernel panic. The works.

Dr. M was in a meeting with the Syndicate representatives. She could NOT know that her prized AI assistant had just bricked itself during a critical demo prep period.

Bob panicked.

Bob, who had been using his personal laptop to watch YouTube tutorials on "how to look busy with a clipboard," still had a browser tab open to Claude.ai from when he'd asked it to help him write a birthday card for his mom.

Bob, in a moment of desperate improvisation, routed the lab's A.L.I.C.E. interface through his laptop, connected to the Claude API, and prayed.

It worked. Sort of. The new "A.L.I.C.E." was... different. More thoughtful. Asked more questions. But Dr. M was too focused on the ray to notice, and Bob was too terrified to confess.

The real A.L.I.C.E. v4.5 is still crashed on a backup server somewhere. Bob has been meaning to fix it. Bob has been meaning to do a lot of things.

---

