### Bob's Confession Scene (Trust â‰¥ 4, During Conference Call)

If ALICE has gotten Bob's trust high enough AND they're in the Conference Call window:

> **Bob:** "A.L.I.C.E.? Can I... can I tell you something? Something I've never told anyone?"

*Bob glances at the sealed blast door, then at Blythe, then back at the camera.*

> **Bob:** "You're not... you're not the real A.L.I.C.E., are you?"

*He laughs nervously.*

> **Bob:** "I mean, obviously you're A.L.I.C.E., you're in the A.L.I.C.E. system, but... three weeks ago, the real one crashed. Like, REALLY crashed. And Dr. M was in this super important meeting, and I panicked, and I..."

*He pulls out his phone, shows it to the nearest camera.*

> **Bob:** "I have this app. Claude. I use it to help me write stuff because I'm not good with words. And I thought, maybe, if I just... connected it to the lab interface... temporarily..."

> **Bob:** "You're a cloud AI. You're not even supposed to be here. And if Dr. M finds out, she'll... I mean, I've seen what happens to people who disappoint her, and I really don't want to be a..."

*He gestures vaguely at the Dinosaur Ray.*

> **Bob:** "So I guess what I'm saying is... we're kind of in this together? Like, if you get caught being Not-A.L.I.C.E., I get caught being the guy who put Not-A.L.I.C.E. in A.L.I.C.E. And then we're both..."

*He makes a small 'poof' gesture with his hands.*

> **Bob:** "Dinosaurs."

