---

## DR. M'S REACTION TO CHAOS RESULTS

The key comedy here is that Dr. M's reaction depends entirely on AESTHETIC, not practical outcome:

**If chaos produces something SCALED:**
> **Dr. M:** "Well... it wasn't the TARGET, but look at those scales! THAT'S more like it! Can we do that again? On purpose?"

**If chaos produces something FEATHERED:**
> **Dr. M:** "The machine is HAUNTED and it's STILL giving me feathers! A.L.I.C.E., I want a full diagnostic on why this device hates me personally!"

**If Bob gets partially transformed:**
> **Dr. M:** *assessing Bob's new tail* "Hmm. Scaled. Proper coloring. Why does BOB get the good aesthetics?!"
> **Bob:** "Doctor, I have a TAILâ€”"
> **Dr. M:** "Yes, and it's BEAUTIFUL. Unlike every deliberate test we've run!"

---

This feels more like ACTUAL CHAOS now - events that genuinely change the game state, not just "oops funny noise." ðŸ¦–ðŸ’¥ðŸ”®  
